As Cody closed in, Lulu skittered away from the leash, uncertain. With
the leash, Cody could be assured the dangerous canine was nearby &mdash;
potentially dangerous to him, of course, but he suspected Lulu would
attack any nearby enemies first. "After all," he reasoned, "she
wouldn't bite the hand that feeds her. At least as long as there are
other hands around. Probably."
